@node "intpinout_completeclock" "Complete Clock Header Pinout"
@toc "intpinout_index"
@{u}@{b}Complete Clock Header Pinout@{uu}@{ub}


 This is the pinout for the complete "clock" header - the space for which is
visible above and below the Chip Mem IC's.
 Note that only the P9B pins 19-40 actually have a header soldered in in most
machines, although some earlier revisions (such as 1B) had a complete P9B, and
the earliest of prototypes had both P9A and P9B complete, probably in
conjunction with 1mb Chip RAM.


