Description by David Bump



                   CPU: 68030              Jumpers:  TEST
   Manufactured Speeds: 30, 40, 50mhz                FPU Speed
            FPU Socket: PGA
           SIMM Socket: 1 x 72-pin
          Total Memory: 128mb

            Autoconfig: No - Utilities supplied
                   MMU: Only on 30mhz and 50mhz
       Real Time Clock: Yes


 Notes:

  Two programs supplied to configure memory. SetXA takes the specification
values as arguments and configures the board at startup (every time), while
AddXAMem automatically adds just the memory every time. A better option is
AutoXA, which installs itself, reboots and configures the memory automatically
on subsequent boots.

 Wait states can also be set with SetXA. It will automatically set the
"proper" value, but this can be overridden.


